ce17f638d8bc00c2db21000a07fad4871422bbed.label: BIGOWLWorkflows Ontology
creator: Aether Group
ce17f638d8bc00c2db21000a07fad4871422bbed.title: BIGOWLWorkflows
ce17f638d8bc00c2db21000a07fad4871422bbed.description: This ontology is used tto guide the correct orchestration of a workflow, including elements like tasks, components, parameters, etc. This ontology imports BIGOWLData and BIGOWLAlgorithms to define all the pieces in a workflow.

creator: José F. Aldana-Martín
2a66995720d344de9e8a8fb0f05397459abceb46.title: moody - Multi-objective Optimization Ontology
2a66995720d344de9e8a8fb0f05397459abceb46.description: moody (Multi-Objective Optimization ontologY) is a OWL2 ontology aiming to provide the ontology model to allow the semantic consolidation of the data related to multi-objective optimization experiments, including algorithms, problems and quality indicators.

9f2a8437caf1aac49b1942c40c4d36cd376a1e42.label: BIGOWLData Ontology
creator: Aether Group
9f2a8437caf1aac49b1942c40c4d36cd376a1e42.title: BIGOWLData
9f2a8437caf1aac49b1942c40c4d36cd376a1e42.description: This ontology contains all the classes and properties related to data. Data is devoted to annotating all the data flowing throughout the analytic workflow. It is declared as EquivalentTo IO-Class of DMOP. This aligning enables datatypes defined by third parties’ ontologies to be contextualised in the analysis. BIGOWLData contains the main data properties defined for this class, namely: path, to annotate the origin of data; and hasDataType, which establishes the relationship with class DataType. This last is used to define the data type, i.e. PrimitiveType (Double, Integer, Boolean, etc.) or StructuredType (Graph, Tree, Matrix, Vector, Tuple, etc.).

a204fa02e3baa08efecc49ccac332cadc759cb49.label: BIGOWL Ontology
creator: Aether Group
a204fa02e3baa08efecc49ccac332cadc759cb49.title: BIGOWL
a204fa02e3baa08efecc49ccac332cadc759cb49.description: BIGOWL (BIG data analytics OWL2 ontology) acts as a formal schema for representing and consolidating knowledge in Big Data analytics. Knowledge incorporation is, in turn, beneficial for efficient algorithmic performance by taking part in the operator’s design, parameter selection, and human interactive and decision-making strategies.

3268308530411688f97fb69831412349806d2240.label: BIGOWLAlgorithms Ontology
creator: Aether Group
3268308530411688f97fb69831412349806d2240.title: BIGOWLAlgorithms
3268308530411688f97fb69831412349806d2240.description: This ontology covers all possible kinds. It has two main subclasses: DataMiningAlgorithm and OptimizationAlgorithm, which are used to distinguish between these two families of algorithms. The former is included in the form of equivalence with the class DM-Algorithm, which is linked from DMOP.

367746046af8964efd0bd6b25d9ad2d6a60fbbeb.label: BIGOWLProblems Ontology
creator: Aether Group
367746046af8964efd0bd6b25d9ad2d6a60fbbeb.title: BIGOWLProblems
367746046af8964efd0bd6b25d9ad2d6a60fbbeb.description: This ontology is used to represent the problem class and its properties. Problem is oriented to the specific problem domain (Smart Cities, Biology, etc.).
